to find transportation for the cheap price some low cost airlines offer. Low cost airlines are EVERYWHERE. Through all South America, Canada, United States and Europe. In Chile you can find passes from $30 (USD) one way to a destination. In U.S. you can find $30 round trip. Throw in cheap hostels and loads of backpackers everywhere, and suddenly Santiago de Chile is a real travel destination.

As for getting from there to the Pacific Coast or Easter Island, the big question is whether you want to go through Central Chile or through Peru. The later is a tad longer, though probably cheaper overall.

It really depends you time you have in hand and budget!
